article.description: Bardo leads Dayton to 21-14 win over Butler
article.headline: Bardo leads Dayton to 21-14 win over Butler
article.linkText: Bardo leads Dayton to 21-14 win over Butler
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS -- Will Bardo threw for 240 yards and two touchdowns and ran for another to lead Dayton to a 21-14 win over Butler on Saturday. Bardo's 28-yard connection with Ross Smith early in the second quarter was the game-winner for the Flyers (7-3, 5-2 Pioneer League). Dayton took a 14-0 lead in the first quarter on Bardo's 27-yard hookup with Cory Stuart and his 1-yard plunge after Zach Elias returned an interception 22 yards to the Butler 28. However the Bulldogs (4-7, 2-6) rallied quickly behind Malcom Weaver. Weaver and Derek O'Connor combined on a 62-yard touchdown with 8 seconds left in the first quarter and then Weaver scored on a 37-yard run at 8:50 of the second. Connor Kacsor had 27 carries for 125 yards for Dayton. O'Connor finished with eight catches for 144 yards as Butler's season came to an end.
